This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with multihop wireless scheduling and proposes a new approach to improve delay performance. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it discusses the optimization of throughput. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it proposes a new algorithm for controlling the link state process. It may also be relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it emphasizes the importance of implementing the algorithm in a distributed manner. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) as it deals with scheduling in a network of multiple agents.
